Description: Neck fragment of large Attic pottery black-figured vessel; interior glazed; exterior, ridge, glazed at centre of sherd; above, frieze of ducks to right; white on wings; below, slight area of glaze at bottom of sherd; graffito on reserved band above it.
Bibliographic references: Vase / Catalogue of Vases in the British Museum (B103.27)
Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GA.1992)
